<br>
Going right to Mars, as Mars Direct does, is good because it's a simple sound bite for the short-attention-span media, politicians or the public. &quot;What's a station for?&quot; or &quot;Why go to an NEA&quot;? they ask, and by the time you start explaining, they've fallen asleep again...<br>
Everybody understands Mars.<br>
